    <h2 id="dosage-guide">Biotin Dosage Guide for Hair Growth</h2>

    <p>Biotin dosage for hair growth is not one-size-fits-all. Your optimal dose depends on your starting biotin status, the severity of hair thinning, and your tolerance for potential side effects.</p>

    <div class="vs-strip">
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>2,500mcg — Entry Level</strong>
        <p>Suitable for mild thinning or preventive supplementation. Lowest risk of acne or lab test interference. Start here if you have never taken biotin before.<br /><em>Best for: Prevention, mild shedding</em></p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>5,000mcg — Sweet Spot</strong>
        <p>The most commonly studied dose for hair growth. Balances efficacy with minimal side effects. Recommended for most users with noticeable hair thinning.<br /><em>Best for: Active hair loss, general thinning</em></p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>10,000mcg — Maximum Dose</strong>
        <p>Highest available concentration. May produce faster results in severely deficient individuals. Higher risk of acne — supplement with B5 to mitigate.<br /><em>Best for: Severe thinning, known biotin deficiency</em></p>
      </div>
    </div>

